article.description: N. Dakota St. 96, S. Dakota St. 74
article.headline: N. Dakota St. 96, S. Dakota St. 74
article.linkText: N. Dakota St. 96, S. Dakota St. 74
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Ben Woodside had 32 points and six assists to lead North Dakota State to a 96-74 win over South Dakota State Tuesday in the Summit League. Woodside had four of NDSU's 12 3-pointers, helping the league-leading Bison (20-6, 14-2) to their sixth straight win over the Jackrabbits (12-16, 7-9). NDSU, which had its 11-game winning streak snapped last week, took the excitement out of it early by grabbing a 45-33 lead at the half. It opened the second half on a 19-6 run. Mike Nelson had four 3-pointers and finished with 18 points. Michael Tveidt had 12 and Brett Winkelman 10 for the Bison. Garrett Callahan had three 3-pointers and led SDSU with 19 points. Dale Moss and Anthony Cordova added 15 points apiece.
